<h1 class="pb-5">DriveHub Admin Portal - Terms of Use</h1>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>These terms govern the use of the DriveHub Admin Portal by staff. By accessing and using this portal, you agree to comply with these terms and any policies or guidelines provided.</p>

<h2>2. User Responsibilities</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Confidentiality</strong>: Maintain the confidentiality of all data accessed through the portal. Do not share sensitive information with unauthorized individuals.</li>
    <li><strong>Data Accuracy</strong>: Ensure all data entered is accurate and up-to-date. Regularly review and correct any discrepancies.</li>
    <li><strong>Access</strong>: Use the portal only for authorized purposes. Do not attempt to access systems or data beyond your clearance level.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Security</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account Security</strong>: Keep your login credentials secure. Do not share your username or password with anyone.</li>
    <li><strong>Reporting Issues</strong>: Immediately report any security breaches, unauthorized access, or suspicious activities to the IT department.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Usage Guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Professional Conduct</strong>: Use the portal in a professional manner at all times. Avoid any actions that could disrupt the operations of the portal.</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance</strong>: Abide by all applicable laws, regulations, and internal policies related to data protection and privacy.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Monitoring and Auditing</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Activity Monitoring</strong>: All activities performed on the portal are subject to monitoring and logging for security and compliance purposes.</li>
    <li><strong>Audit</strong>: Regular audits will be conducted to ensure compliance with these terms.</li>
</ul>

